{"parse":{"title":"Social and behavior change communication","pageid":26877546,"revid":846266323,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Behavior_Intervention_by_using_Images.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/3f/Behavior_Intervention_by_using_Images.jpg/220px-Behavior_Intervention_by_using_Images.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"105\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/3f/Behavior_Intervention_by_using_Images.jpg/330px-Behavior_Intervention_by_using_Images.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/3/3f/Behavior_Intervention_by_using_Images.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"389\" data-file-height=\"185\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Behavior_Intervention_by_using_Images.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>SBCC by health practitioner</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Development-Entertainment_Continuum.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/Development-Entertainment_Continuum.png/220px-Development-Entertainment_Continuum.png\" width=\"220\" height=\"120\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/Development-Entertainment_Continuum.png/330px-Development-Entertainment_Continuum.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/Development-Entertainment_Continuum.png/440px-Development-Entertainment_Continuum.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"2054\" data-file-height=\"1117\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Development-Entertainment_Continuum.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>SBCC on the Development-Entertainment spectrum.</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Social and behavior change communication</b> (<b>SBCC</b>), often also only \"<b>BCC</b>\" or \"<b>Communication for Development</b> (<b>C4D</b>)\" is an interactive process of any intervention with <a href=\"/wiki/Individuals\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Individuals\">individuals</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Communities\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Communities\">communities</a> and/or societies (as integrated with an overall program) to develop <a href=\"/wiki/Communication\" title=\"Communication\">communication</a> strategies to promote positive behaviors which are appropriate to their settings and there by solve worlds most pressing health problems. This in turn provides a supportive environment which will enable people to initiate, sustain and maintain positive and desirable <a href=\"/wiki/Behavior\" title=\"Behavior\">behavior</a> outcomes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-UNFPA_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-UNFPA-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>SBCC is the strategic use of communication to promote positive health outcomes, based on proven theories and models of <a href=\"/wiki/Behavior_change_(public_health)\" title=\"Behavior change (public health)\">behavior change</a>. SBCC employs a systematic process beginning with formative research and behavior analysis, followed by communication planning, implementation, and monitoring and evaluation. Audiences are carefully segmented, messages and materials are pre-tested, and mass media (which include radio, television, billboards, print material, internet), interpersonal channels (such as client-provider interaction, group presentations) and community mobilisation are used to achieve defined behavioral objectives.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>BCC should not be confused with <a href=\"/wiki/Behavior_modification\" title=\"Behavior modification\">behavior modification</a>, a term with specific meaning in a <a href=\"/wiki/Clinical_psychiatry\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Clinical psychiatry\">clinical psychiatry</a> setting.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Background\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Background</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Steps\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Steps</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Enabling_factors\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Enabling factors</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Theories\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Theories</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Strategies\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Strategies</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Implications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Implications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Role_in_HIV/AIDS\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Role in HIV/AIDS</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">8</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">9</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">10</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Background\">Background</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Social_and_behavior_change_communication&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Background\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Providing people with information and teaching them how they should behave does not lead to desirable change in their response/behavior. However, when there is a supportive environment with information and communication (teaching) then there is a desirable change in the behavior of the target group. Thus, SBCC is proved to be an instructional intervention which has a close interface with education and communication. It is a strategic and group oriented form of communication to perceive a desired change in behavior of target group.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>However, it is not as easy as it sounds, as there is no one-size-fits all strategy for any intervention. Interventions are context specific. Therefore, there is a need for proper information management and sharing. It is advised to document and report the interventions that worked somewhere, for example, the kind of messages, the medium and the audience.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Steps\">Steps</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Social_and_behavior_change_communication&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Steps\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>SBCC is the comprehensive process in which one passes through the stages:\n</p><p>Unaware\n&gt; Aware\n&gt; Concerned\n&gt; Knowledgeable\n&gt; Motivated to change\n&gt; Practicing trial behavior change\n</p><p>\n&gt; Sustained behavior change</p><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Behavior_Change_Communication.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b2/Behavior_Change_Communication.jpg/220px-Behavior_Change_Communication.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"180\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/b/b2/Behavior_Change_Communication.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"307\" data-file-height=\"251\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Behavior_Change_Communication.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>SBCC in classroom practices</div></div></div>\n<p>It involves the following steps:<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ol><li>State program goals</li>\n<li>Involve stakeholders</li>\n<li>Identify target populations</li>\n<li>Conduct formative BCC assessments</li>\n<li>Segment target populations</li>\n<li>Define behavior change objectives</li>\n<li>Define SBCC strategy &amp; monitoring and evaluation plan</li>\n<li>Develop communication products</li>\n<li>Pretest</li>\n<li>Implement and monitor</li>\n<li>Evaluate</li>\n<li>Analyze feedback and revise</li></ol>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Enabling_factors\">Enabling factors</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Social_and_behavior_change_communication&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Enabling factors\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Behavior change is influenced by motivation from others (external influence) as well as from within oneself (internal influence). Internal influence plays a significant role in creating more enjoyment of a behavior change, instilling a sense of ownership of the new behavior, which in turn instills a sense of ownership of the changed behavior.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> When designing SBCC strategies, enabling factors that affect the outcome must be considered. The following are some of the factors:<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Effective communication</li>\n<li>Enabling environment, which include policies, human rights community values and norms</li>\n<li>User-friendly, accessible services and commodities</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Theories\">Theories</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Social_and_behavior_change_communication&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Theories\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>SBCC has several levels at which it can be implemented. Each level includes several theories. Each level (and each theory) employs specific communication channels.\n</p>\n<dl><dt>Individual level</dt></dl>\n<ul><li>Health belief theory</li>\n<li>Theory of reasoned action and planned behavior</li>\n<li>Stages of change</li>\n<li>Social learning</li></ul>\n<dl><dt>Community level</dt></dl>\n<ul><li>Diffusion of innovations theory</li>\n<li>Community mobilization</li></ul>\n<dl><dt>Change in organizations</dt></dl>\n<ul><li>4 stage change</li></ul>\n<dl><dt>Public policy Level</dt></dl>\n<ul><li>Distinct stages of initiation, action, implementation, evaluation and re-formulation</li></ul>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:SBCC_Summit_in_Bali_2018.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/SBCC_Summit_in_Bali_2018.jpg/220px-SBCC_Summit_in_Bali_2018.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/SBCC_Summit_in_Bali_2018.jpg/330px-SBCC_Summit_in_Bali_2018.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/SBCC_Summit_in_Bali_2018.jpg/440px-SBCC_Summit_in_Bali_2018.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4032\" data-file-height=\"3024\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:SBCC_Summit_in_Bali_2018.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The SBCC Summit 2018 in Bali, Indonesia, focusing on social and behavior change communication and featuring <a href=\"/wiki/Entertainment-Education\" title=\"Entertainment-Education\">Entertainment-Education</a>.</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:SBCC_Summit_2018_Crowd_in_Nusa_Dua,_Indonesia.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/43/SBCC_Summit_2018_Crowd_in_Nusa_Dua%2C_Indonesia.jpg/220px-SBCC_Summit_2018_Crowd_in_Nusa_Dua%2C_Indonesia.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"110\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/43/SBCC_Summit_2018_Crowd_in_Nusa_Dua%2C_Indonesia.jpg/330px-SBCC_Summit_2018_Crowd_in_Nusa_Dua%2C_Indonesia.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/43/SBCC_Summit_2018_Crowd_in_Nusa_Dua%2C_Indonesia.jpg/440px-SBCC_Summit_2018_Crowd_in_Nusa_Dua%2C_Indonesia.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"7648\" data-file-height=\"3824\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:SBCC_Summit_2018_Crowd_in_Nusa_Dua,_Indonesia.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Over 1,200 attendees came to the 2018 SBCC Summit, where Entertainment-Education was a main topic among Social and Behavior Chance Communications professionals.</div></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Strategies\">Strategies</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Social_and_behavior_change_communication&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Strategies\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>SBCC is different from the ordinary instructional method of communication and is target specific. A society consists of many sub-groups. The strategy for SBCC will vary from group to group. The following points are important while considering the SBCC strategy.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BCC_AIDS_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BCC_AIDS-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Vulnerability/risk factor of the target group</li>\n<li>The vulnerability/risk factor of the group which is to be addressed</li>\n<li>The conflict and obstacles in the way to desired change in behavior</li>\n<li>Type of message and communication media which can best be used to reach the target group</li>\n<li>Type of resources available and assessment of existing knowledge of the target group about the issue which is going to be dealt with</li></ul>\n<p>There can be several more points in this list. A successful SBCC requires lots of research and meticulous planning about the knowledge content of the subject and behavior/attitude pattern of the target group.<sup id=\"cite_ref-UNFPA_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-UNFPA-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Social_marketing\" title=\"Social marketing\">Social marketing</a> has been described as a tool for <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Sustainable_behaviour&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Sustainable behaviour (page does not exist)\">sustainable behaviour</a> change.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Implications\">Implications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Social_and_behavior_change_communication&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Implications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>SBCC has proven effective in several health areas, such as increasing the use of family planning methods,reducing the spread of malaria and other infectious diseases, and improving newborn and maternal health.\n</p><p>SBCC is an effective tool for dealing with many community and group related problems. BCC has been adapted as an effective strategy for <a href=\"/wiki/Community_mobilization\" title=\"Community mobilization\">community mobilization</a>, health  and environment education and various public outreach programs.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\nEnhanced knowledge about the behavior change process has facilitated the design of communications programs to reduce the risk of HIV transmission and AIDS. A wide variety of health promotion strategies use communication as either an educational or norm-forming strategy. In addition, specific strategies must be designed for high-risk groups such as women, young people, injecting drug abusers, homosexuals and HIV positive groups.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BCC_AIDS_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BCC_AIDS-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Role_in_HIV.2FAIDS\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Role_in_HIV/AIDS\">Role in HIV/AIDS</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Social_and_behavior_change_communication&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: Role in HIV/AIDS\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>SBCC constitutes of effective communication which is central to the success of interventions to reduce the risk of HIV infection. It plays a role to:<sup id=\"cite_ref-BCC_AIDS_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BCC_AIDS-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Increase knowledge</li>\n<li>Stimulate community dialogue</li>\n<li>Promote essential attitude change</li>\n<li>Advocate for policy changes</li>\n<li>Create a demand for information and services</li>\n<li>Reduce stigma and discrimination</li>\n<li>Promote services for prevention and care</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Social_and_behavior_change_communication&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Attitude_change\" title=\"Attitude change\">Attitude change</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Behavior_change_(public_health)\" title=\"Behavior change (public health)\">Behavior change (public health)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Entertainment-Education\" title=\"Entertainment-Education\">Entertainment-Education</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Design_for_behaviour_change\" title=\"Design for behaviour change\">Design for behaviour change</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Johns_Hopkins_University_Center_for_Communication_Programs\" title=\"Johns Hopkins University Center for Communication Programs\">Johns Hopkins University Center for Communication Programs</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Social_and_behavior_change_communication&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-UNFPA-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-UNFPA_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-UNFPA_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\"><a rel=\"